item.title: Orphaned case 17
item.dc:creator: @hidendra Hidendra
item.description:
@hidendra wrote:

orphaned case is when you have a case statement outside of a switch… you have too many braces in the case above it somewhere… example of orphaned case :

switch(int) {
    case 1:
        continue;
}
case 2:
    return;

item.description:

[quote=“The Soul, post:10, topic:273703”][quote author=jc22493 link=topic=361692.msg2749993#msg2749993 date=1239842810]

You have a duplicate of a case in the same switch statement.

JC, you should know better

Post the case directly above case 17, and I will tell you the fix. You just have a “}” or a “break;” out of place.

Orphaned case means that you have a duplicate.
[/quote]

If there were more than one of the same case ID in a switch statement, it would then throw the ‘duplicate case label’ error.[/quote]
